The paper deals with image forgery detection, which is a topic closely related to computer vision (cs.CV). The use of autoencoder-based architecture and Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) also suggests that the paper may fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.MM), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper's focus on transferability and domain adaptation may also place it under the sub-category of learning theory (cs.LG).
